cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the downlink analysis of cellular networks, which falls under the networking domain. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the performance of non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) and orthogonal multiple access (OMA) techniques, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with the analysis of cellular networks and resource allocation techniques, which are related to communication systems. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the performance of different service models and resource allocation techniques, which are related to control systems. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the mean packet delay and effective capacity, which are related to multimedia applications.
